Class ShopSimulation

    • Constructor Detail

      • ShopSimulation

        public ShopSimulation​(int seed,
                      int numOfSv,
                      int numOfSelf,
                      int maxQueue,
                      int numOfCus,
                      double arrivalRate,
                      double serviceRate,
                      double restingRate,
                      double probRest,
                      double probGreedy)
        Creates a new ShopSimulation with a RandomGenerator, servers, arriving customers, probability of rest for servers and greedy customers. While setting the maximum queue number of all the servers.
        Parameters:
        seed - The seed for the RandomGenerator
        numOfSv - The number of servers to be generated.
        numOfSelf - The number of self-check counters.
        maxQueue - The maximum number of customers allowed to wait in the queue.
        numOfCus - The number of customers that arrived.
        arrivalRate - The rate of arrival for the RandomGenerator.
        serviceRate - The rate of service for the RandomGenerator.
        restingRate - The rate of resting for human servers for the RandomGenerator.
        probRest - The probability of human server resting.
        probGreedy - The probability of the greedy customer.

      • processArrival

        public CustomerEvent processArrival​(ArriveEvent ae,
                                    Server sv)
        Process ArriveEvent with three scenarios: (i) The customer would be served immediately. (ii) The customer would be placed on the waiting list. (iii) The customer would leave if the server cannot serve or the customer cannot wait.
        Parameters:
        ae - The ArriveEvent
        sv - The server to either serve, place the customer on wait or cause the customer to leave.
        Returns:
        A CustomerEvent (ServedEvent/LeaveEvent/WaitEvent).
